				 																MUSIC				 																																	 December 29 - 31 at Gyan Manch; 6 pm: Nehru Childrens Museum presents a festival of dance, song and recitation, and dance-drama Janani Janmabhumi, by the children from nearby districts of Calcutta along with the children of Nehru Childrens Museum.				 																																	 December 29 at Kala Mandir; 6 pm: Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan presents a vocal duet by Naveen Namboodri and Kumar Mukherjee, and a ballet, Chetonar Kumortuli, conceived and choreographed by Vandana Alase Hazra and performed by her students.				 																																	 December 31 at G.D. Birla Sabhagar; 6 pm: An evening of classical music featuring Ashish Khan and Swapan Choudhury.				 																																	 January 1 at Kala Mandir basement; 6 pm: In memory of Ustad Aziz Khan, Swarshruti presents an evening of classical music featuring Ustad Shahid Parvez Khan (sitar) and Rupali Dalal (vocal).				 																																	 January 3 at Kala Mandir; 5 pm: The 17th session of Balyygunge Music Conference features Ustad Amjad Ali Khan (sarod), Ustad Rashid Khan (vocal) and Saswati Sen (Kathak).				 																																	 January 3 at Science City main auditorium; 6 pm: In aid of Niladri Health on Wheels (a medical clinic), Sri Gouranga Ashram presents an evening of music concert featuring L. Subramaniam (violin), Bhupinder Singh and Mitalee (vocal) and Sivamani and Govinda (music of the drums).				 																DANCE				 																																	 December 29 at Rang Manch Bharatiyam Cultural Multiplex, Salt Lake; 6 pm: Lok Nritya Samaroha featuring Bihu, Purulia chhau and Rabha.				 																																	 December 30 at Kala Mandir; 6.30 pm: Samskritiki Shreyaskar, as part of its eighth anniversary celebrations, presents Khoi Nadi (a dance drama for and by children; conceived and choreographed by Rani Karnaa) and Kathak Anek Rang (an exposition of the aspects of Kathak